                    <comment id="12763542" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 17:09:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;simple patch, but will need to warn in CHANGES.txt that folks should reindex, if they are using non-Arabic stopwords.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12763546" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 17:24:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;if no one objects, I&apos;d like to commit this for 3.0 at the end of the day.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12763552" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 17:33:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;here also update the javadocs to reflect the new order of what is going on in ArabicAnalyzer, to prevent any confusion to users.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12763554" author="dmsmith" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 17:40:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;can you commit it to 2.9.1 too? (For those stuck on Java 1.4, there is no 3.0).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12763562" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 18:07:06 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;can you commit it to 2.9.1 too? (For those stuck on Java 1.4, there is no 3.0). &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;can someone comment on this one for me. &lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t think its too much of a stretch to consider this a bug, even if it does not affect Arabic text.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12764002" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2009 13:59:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 823534.&lt;br/&gt;
(if it is ok to apply this to 2.9 branch as DM requested, we should reopen)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12764013" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2009 14:16:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Your issue - if you can stretch it to bugish territory, I&apos;d +1 it. I&apos;d be wary of getting into porting features to 2.9.1 - but I wouldn&apos;t have a problem with this one myself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12764015" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2009 14:22:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Mark, I think the problem is really that I overlooked this use case in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1758&quot; title=&quot;improve arabic analyzer: light8 -&amp;gt; light10&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1758&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, because Arabic is not case sensitive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It won&apos;t affect the default usage of the Analyzer (where all the stopwords are in Arabic and lowercase is a no-op).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am going to also set fix for 2.9.1 and give a day or two for people to comment if they disagree with applying to 2.9 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12765581" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 14 Oct 2009 15:27:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;its been a few days, no one objected to applying this fix to the branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but I do not have permissions to commit to the branch... can someone commit this for me? Attached is the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12765803" author="mikemccand" created="Thu, 15 Oct 2009 00:01:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed on 2.9.x.  Thanks Robert!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12774613" author="mikemccand" created="Sat, 7 Nov 2009 14:57:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close all 2.9.1 issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
